<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Thiago Silva is lapping up the last of the summer sunshine before his attention turns to his first season with Chelsea. </p>

<p>The veteran defender is enjoying a break in Sardinia with his wife Isabela, who posted a picture of them on a boat off the coast. </p>

<p>Silva played his last game for PSG in the Champions League final defeat by Bayern Munich before signing with the Blues as a free agent. </p>

<p>Thiago Silva (right) and his wife Isabela are enjoying a holiday before flying to London </p>

<p>Frank Lampard has afforded the 35-year-old some extended time off to recover and he is recharging the batteries in idyllic surroundings. </p>

<p>His wife shared two snaps of them both in swimming gear and wrote the caption: 'It's beautiful when someone chooses to stay when they can leave. </p>

<p>'I never looked for perfection, and we are that, the “imperfect” choice, but surely, the most certain thing we did in life, I love you.'</p>

<p>The couple are in Sardinia and Silva has been given time off after the Champions League final </p>

<p>Silva penned a one-year deal with Chelsea after his PSG contract expired last season</p>

<p>Silva completed his medical in Milan before jetting off for a break. </p>

<p>He joined on a one-year deal and is expected to slot into the heart of the defence. The Brazilian is part of a new look Chelsea side with Roman Abramovich having splashed £231million on Timo Werner, Hakim Ziyech, Ben Chilwell and Kai Havertz with Malang Sarr signing on a free. </p>

<p>After the deal for Silva was completed he told the club's website: 'I am so happy to be joining Chelsea.</p>

<p>'I am delighted to be a part of Frank Lampard's exciting squad for next season and I'm here to challenge for honours. See you soon Chelsea fans, I look forward to playing at Stamford Bridge very soon.'</p>

<p>Silva's final game for PSG was the Champions League final defeat by Bayern Munich </p>
